Lloyds Bank May Sell More Current Accounts, FT Reports

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-09-05T04:20:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/lloyds-bank-may-sell-more-current-accounts-ft-reports.html
Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  may sell
more current accounts than will be recommended under the
forthcoming Independent Commission on Banking report, the
Financial Times reported, citing people close to the situation.  Lloyds plans to offer current accounts through its C&G
homeloans unit, which it plans to sell along with 632 branches
and a 4.6 percent share of current accounts, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Peterson in London on 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  